getSettingsPath

public static java.lang.String getSettingsPath(User user)
Returns the path where the settings for the specified User are kept. Returns null if the specified User is new and his settings weren't saved yet.

loadUser

public static User loadUser(java.lang.String path)
Loads a User from the specified path. The path is not guaranteed to be local - it may be a URL to a remote location. Returns null if unable to load from the specified path.

saveUser

public static java.lang.String saveUser(User user)
Saves the given User. If this is yet an unknown User and the user doesn't abort the save, it is added to the list of known users. If the process fails for some reason, an appropriate message is displayed to the user, so the caller needn't worry about that. The returned String is the path into which the User was saved, or null if the saving process failed.
